[Article in Russian]

Malygina NA(1), Melent'ev AS, Kostomarova IV, Melent'ev IA, Saégitov RT, 
Smirnova IuB, Serova LD.

Author information:
(1)derjagin@ium.ips.ras.ru

Allele and genotype frequencies of the HindIII polymorphism of the lipoprotein 
lipase (LPL) gene were studied in patients with myocardial infarction (MI) and 
stable angina of effort (SAE), including long-lived people (over 90). The 
polymorphism proved to be associated with MI and with the life span, genotype 
H+/H+ being predisposing to MI and allele H- being protective. The allele and 
genotype frequencies of long-lived people differed significantly from the 
