(1)Cattedra di Igiene, Università degli Studi di Cassino, Italia.

The state of health of the world population has costantly improved in recent 
years. However, quality of life and life expectancy show huge variations in the 
different demografic regions of the world. To explain such differences three 
main factors can be considered: 1 - patterns of disease, which are largely 
determined by geography and climate; 2 - human behaviour; 3 - health services 
funding, organization and management. The paper develops a discussion on these 
issues, focusing on correlation between health systems methods of funding and 
management and state of health of the world population.

